application

Class DataHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.DataHandler

  • public class DataHandler
extends java.lang.Object
    Takes data and puts it into a MatchData object. Stores an array of all the MatchData and handles turning it into a CSV format. Keeps track of what has been written to a file and removes it from the array ofMatchData that hasn't been written (the notWritten array) while keeping all the data in an array called allData
    Author:
    Aidan Sciortino

        Adds a new MatchData object to the notWritten array.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the team for the MatchData Object
        teamNumber - Number of the team for the MatchData Object
        matchNumber - Match number for the MatchData Object
        alliance - Which alliance the team is on for the MatchData object (true = red, false = blue)
        autoBaseline - Whether or not the team crosses the baseline this match
        autoHighFuel - Whether or not the team shot fuel into the high goal in auto this match
        autoLowFuel - Whether or not the team shot fuel into the low goal in auto this match
        kPaAuto - How many kPa the team scored in auto this match
        autoLeftGear - Whether or not the team went for the left gear peg in auto this match
        autoLeftGearFailed - Whether or not they failed the left gear peg in auto
        autoCenterGear - Whether or not the team went for the center gear peg in auto this match
        autoCenterGearFailed - Whether or not they failed the center gear peg in auto
        autoRightGear - Whether or not the team went for the right gear peg in auto this match
        autoRightGearFailed - Whether or not they failed the right gear peg in auto
        matchGearsPlaced - How many gears the team placed this match
        matchGearsFailed - How many gears the team failed to place this match
        kPaScored - How many kPa the team scored this match
        climbed - Whether or not the team climbed this match
        climbFailed - Whether or not the team attempted the climb but didn't activate the touchpad
        climbNoAttempt - Whether or not the team did not attempt to climb this match
        climbMalfunction - Whether or not the team had a malfunction with their climber this match
        notes - Further notes on a team's match performance
